    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive containers, usually made of animal hide and decorated with beadwork or quillwork. A major feature of Midewiwin ceremonies practiced by Ojibwe, Odawa, Santee, and other Great Lakes Native North American tribes. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
